This paper belongs to the field of computational linguistics (cs.CL) as it focuses on analyzing linguistic patterns in a large French Twitter corpus. Additionally, the paper also incorporates socioeconomic data, which suggests that it could also fall under the categories of social networks (cs.SOC) and social informatics (cs.SI). The use of multivariate analysis techniques to analyze the data could also place it under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper's focus on language and communication could also make it relevant to the field of computational linguistics and natural language processing (cs.CY).
